secondary_outcome.description:
The (Dutch) Productivity Cost Questionnaire (iPCQ) will be used to measure the impact of disease on the ability of a person to perform work, either employed or unemployed.
It is divided into 3 categories:
absences of work measured in days from 0 to 28 days or more, either employed or unemployed;
the cost of productivity loss for participants and the employees will be calculated by the friction cost method and the human capital method. Higher scores mean more production loss, for employed participants;
The cost of productivity loss from unpaid work is calculated by multiplying the amount of productivity loss by a standard hourly rate of household care. Higher scores mean more production loss, for unemployed participants;
